Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal concentrating ability and possible nephrotic or diabetic kidney involvement. No evidence of urinary tract infection is present. Liver function and electrolytes are within normal limits. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and assessment for underlying causes of acute or chronic kidney disease.
